      <heading>Sun Jun 10 (Iavoe)      :: &amp;gRetirement*n</heading>
      <slot>14</slot>
      <level>199</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Word passes along the usualy channels of High Captain Iavoe Kindar's
retirement from active duty as a member of the Tower Guard. His second
in command has moved to fill the position left by the long time officer
for the time being, though only the Hall of the Tower and the Amyrlin
Seat herself know for sure what is to happen with the military force.

Regardless of the state of the army of Tar Valon though, rumors say
that though Iavoe has retired from active duty he will still be a
presence within the White Tower. Apparently the man's life has become
quite attached to the White Tower in the decades he has spent in it's
service. So it seems he will be floating around as an occasional
advisor and purveyor of wisdom and strategy to whomever fills his
shoes within the Tower Guard, and may be found in his old offices
or on the training grounds, if he is within the White Tower's walls.
It is said he spoke to some of his officer's of travelling and perhaps
learning of other military groups and training styles, and has left
a contact in Caemlyn where they may send word to him in the case of
emergencies.

Whatever the real truths of the situation may be, it is clear that
things have changed within the Tower Guard and that one of it's oldest
officers will no longer play the role he once did.
</text>
