      <heading>Wed Feb  6 (Nora)       :: Catastrophe</heading>
      <slot>19</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Chaos and destruction erupted in the Yellow Ajah Halls late last night
as large amounts of Saidar were felt being channeled from the rooms of
Jaiana Sedai and followed by the sudden outward collapse of a good 
portion of the hallway walls. When the rubble was cleared enough to
allow entrance, the Mistress of Novices was discovered barely concious
and severely hurt, along with Aidan, Sergeant of the Tower guard and a
common visitor to the Aes Sedai's rooms. After further clean up, two
corpses were found. One was the body of Lauriana, a Novice and former
Rebel, and was gruesome to behold as her head was in too many pieces
to have been the work of the collapsed walls. The other was that of an
as yet unidentified man, whom many had watched Lauriana guide through
the Tower in the scant minutes before the catastrophe.

Further investigation of the matter has turned up two assassinated
guards at Rose Gate, who were believed to have been killed shortly
before Lauriana and the man were seen inside the Tower.  The exact
cause of their death has yet to be determined, but use of the One
Power is believed to be involved.  Both Jaiana Sedai and the Sergeant
have given the story that the dead man had shown up at Jaiana Sedai's
door, and threatened Jaiana's life, showing himself to be a male
channeler by killing Lauriana before attacking. During the fight, the
man apparently over-exhausted himself and ended his own existance in a
decidedly messy manner, causing a number of the wards in Jaiana Sedai's
rooms to trigger and only make a bad situation worse.  Belinda Sedai
has testified that she saw Lauriana and the man standing out in the
hallway outside of Jaiana Sedai's rooms, trying to speak with whomever
was inside, thus lending support to Jaiana and Aidan's claims.

Repairs to the Yellow Ajah Halls and other damaged areas are underway.
The duties of the Mistress of Novices are being overseen by Melanie
Sedai while Jaiana Sedai recovers.  Jaiana Sedai has taken up temporary
residence in her own offices until her rooms are once more habitable.
The Lieutenant suffered only minor injuries and has since returned to
active duty.  Neither he nor Jaiana Sedai are being brought before
the Hall, as they are thus far believed to be cleared of any wrong-
doing in this incident.
</text>
    </message>
