      <heading>Tue Aug 13 (Khalis)     :: &amp;RRules and Regulations&amp;W: Warder Training (Revised)&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>22</slot>
      <level>199</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>1. No trainee below the rank of Student will bear steel without the 
   express consent of a fully-ranked Gaidin.

2. Aspirants may only associate with Novices and Accepted while 
   supervised. Students may associate with Novices and Accepted while
   unsupervised, but only in public locations.

3. No Aspirant, Student, or Protege may leave Tar Valon unless 
   accompanied by a fully-ranked Gaidin or without the express consent 
   of an Aes Sedai.

4. No Aspirant or Student may consume alcoholic beverages.

5. No student may fail to show respect to those of higher rank or to 
   Novices, Accepted, and Aes Sedai.

OOC NOTE: These rules are IC rules, and not in any way an enforcement 
of RP.  A student may choose to break the rules ICly at any time, with 
no fear of OOC punishment.  Only IC consequences will result, and that 
only if the student is caught.  Common courtesy will be strictly 
enforced in that regard, as in, private RP CANNOT be intruded upon 
without the consent of all parties involved.  Therefore, anyone RPing a 
rule-breaking who does not wish to be caught OOCly will not be.  The 
only addendum to this is public places, in which anyone can join RP.  
Locations such as the Training Yards and Salidar Square are presumed to 
be inhabited at all hours, thus, supervision in those places is 
assumed.  The NPCing of fully-ranked characters is not allowed.
</text>
    </message>
